, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hussey-","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: of Norman origin, a nickname for someone who habitually wore a distinctive pair of boots or gaiters, from Old French <i>hosed</i>, <i>hoset</i>, <i>housé</i>, Middle English <i>hosey</i>, <i>hus(s)y</i>,‘booted, gaitered’ (from Latin <i>hosatus</i>).","English: status name or nickname from Middle English <i>hus(e)wyf</i> ‘mistress of a family; wife of a householder’ (a compound of Old English <i>hūs</i> ‘house’ + <i>wīf</i> ‘woman’). Though originally a woman's name, it is often found as a male surname, presumably in a derogatory sense. The vocabulary word became <i>hussie</i>, with the meaning ‘disreputable woman’, in the 16th century; the surname, however, is not associated with this meaning.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hEodhusa</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eodhus</i>’. This was the name of a bardic family associated with the Maguires of Fermanagh, also Anglicized as   Oswell   or   Oswald  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hosea","meanings":["English: variant of   Hussey  . Similarity with the Old Testament prophet's name Hosea (see 3 below) is accidental.","English: in Scotland, where the name is more common, it is sometimes a variant of   Hosie  , itself a form of   Hussey  , or else a variant of   Hossack  .","African (mainly Nigeria and Tanzania): from the Biblical personal name <i>Hosea</i>. In the Old Testament, Hosea was a prophet who married a prostitute in order to illustrate Israel's unfaithfulness to God."]},{"name":"Hosie","meanings":["Scottish (northeast Scotland): variant of Irish   Hussey  ."]},{"name":"Hassey","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Hussey  ."]},{"name":"Oswell","meanings":["English: variant of   Oswald  .","Irish (Ulster): adopted as an English equivalent of Gaelic <b>Ó hEodhusa</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eodhus</i>’ (see   Hussey  )."]},{"name":"Hosey","meanings":["English: variant of   Hussey  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Hussey- was born in 1540, in London, England, United Kingdom. He married Margaret Ball about 1594, in Edmondsham, Dorset, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1600, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1540–1600":"1540–1600","1545–1665":"1545–1665","1595–1625":"1595–1625","1600":"1600","1545":"1545","1665":"1665","1540":"1540","1595":"1595","Abt. 1594":"umbes 1594","About 1595":"umbes 1595","1625":"1625","Edmondsham, Dorset, England":"Edmondsham, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, England":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dorset, England":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1540–1600":"1540–1600","1545–1665":"1545–1665","1595–1625":"1595–1625","1600":"1600","1545":"1545","1665":"1665","1540":"1540","1595":"1595","Abt. 1594":"noin 1594","About 1595":"noin 1595","1625":"1625","Edmondsham, Dorset, England":"Edmondsham, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","London, England":"London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dorset, England":"Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1540–1600":"1540–1600","1545–1665":"1545–1665","1595–1625":"1595–1625","1600":"1600","1545":"1545","1665":"1665","1540":"1540","1595":"1595","Abt. 1594":"environ 1594","About 1595":"environ 1595","1625":"1625","Edmondsham, Dorset, England":"Edmondsham, Dorset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","London, England":"Londres, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Dorset, En